—ЩKarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/let.mdЩ@c747a4e17ccda9b2762d421de2d8cd56683667a37a0361f6e701fab256bcbcbfЄtitle: let‘ЁExamplesЪЊSet a variable to a value (no output).
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> let x = 10


```
Set a variable to the result of an expression (no output).
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> let x = 10 + 100


```
Set a variable based on the condition (no output).
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> let x = if false { -1 } else { 1 }


```
Set a variable to the output of a pipeline.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> ls | let files


```
Use let in the middle of a pipeline to assign and pass the value.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 10 | let x | $x + 5
15

```
Use let in the middle of a pipeline, then consume value with $in.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 10 | let x | $in + 5
15

```
